snippet.textDisplay: At 7 minutes you said using cold air on bleach will make it  work less BECAUSE its an exothermic process, BUT an exothermic process doesnt consume heat, it creates it, so the only way cold air can influence the process is the fact that cold air make the particles move less which results in less reaction. The slower process isnt inherently caused by the exothermic profile of the reaction.

snippet.textDisplay:
My friend and I decided to bleach our hair in a dumb impulse and didn't wear gloves because we forgot to buy them (and it was too late to go get them by then).
THAT. SHIT. HURTTTT
It got under our nails and gosh it hurt so bad! I could barely touch grab/touch anything without it hurting. Turning on my phone felt like needles under my nails. It was as if someone had simultanously closed the door in each of my fingers
(It did look great lol we dyed it like a plum-is purple afterwards and it turned out very nice)
